Method Detail

endVisit

int endVisit()
endVisit can be called to end the current visit and start a new visit. This will flush all pending events to the dynaTrace server.

Returns:
DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOn if the visit is ended successfully, CPWR_Error_NotInitialized if DynatraceUEM has not been initialized

leaveAction

int leaveAction()
Call this method to complete this action and the related data is prepared for sending to the backend database. Note that leaving an outer action would cause all inner actions be completed also.

Returns:
DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOn, otherwise one of the following: DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ActionEnded, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_NotInitialized, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOff

reportEvent

int reportEvent(java.lang.String eventName)
This event reports the time that the event occurred, relating to the session start time. This event can be used to determine when a user passed through a particular view or activity in your application. Configure the reportEvent, specifying the name of the item you wish to capture. A time stamp is added to the event and this data is sent back to the backend database. The reportEvent is a simple way to track user behavior in your application.

Parameters:
eventName - 1 to 240 character event name
Returns:
DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOn, otherwise one of the following: DynatraceUEM.CPWR_InvalidParameter, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ActionEnded, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_NotInitialized, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOff

reportValue

int reportValue(java.lang.String valueName,
                int value)
This event reports a user-defined integer value at any user-defined time in the application lifecycle. For example, if your application receives a variable amount of data each time it makes a request for data, it may be useful to report the number of pieces of data received each time the request is made. In this case, after the application receives the data, the reportValue event returns the data back to the backend database.

Parameters:
valueName - 1 to 240 character value name
value - an integer value from Integer.MIN_VALUE through Integer.MAX_VALUE
Returns:
DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOn, otherwise one of the following: DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ActionEnded, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_NotInitialized, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOff, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_InvalidParameter

reportError

int reportError(java.lang.String errorName,
                int errorCode)
The Report Error event reports a user-defined integer value at any user-defined time in the application lifecycle. The Report Error event is different from the Custom (integer) Value event in that it is specifically identified as an error type of event. The integer value would most likely contain an error code.

Parameters:
errorName - 1 to 120 character error name
errorCode - integer error code
Returns:
DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOn, otherwise one of the following: DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_InvalidParameter, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ActionEnded, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_NotInitialized, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOff, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ReportErrorOff

reportError

int reportError(java.lang.String errorName,
                java.lang.Throwable throwable)
The Report Error event reports a throwable or handled exception at any user-defined time in the application lifecycle. The Report Error event is different from the Custom (string) Value event or reportEvent in that it is specifically identified as an error type of event. The throwable would most likely be a handled exception. Note that this method reports the error outside of the context of an action.

Parameters:
errorName - 1 to 120 character error name
throwable - a caught exception
Returns:
DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOn, otherwise one of the following: DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_InvalidParameter, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ActionEnded, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_NotInitialized, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOff, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ReportErrorOff

tagRequest

int tagRequest(org.apache.http.HttpRequest request)
This method associates the request object to this action. By tagging the request object you will be able to trace the web request from within this action to the backend servers.

Parameters:
request - object to tag
Returns:
DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOn, otherwise one of the following: DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_InvalidParameter, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_ActionEnded, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_Error_NotInitialized, DynatraceUEM.CPWR_UemOff

tagRequest
